        impact: "The project has reframed co-op from being “just” a placement engine to a structured, measurable learning and assessment system, giving Northeastern an evidence-based roadmap for improving co-op quality, targeting equity gaps, and designing real-time supports. It has also surfaced specific levers—specialization, task complexity, supervision quality—that are now being built into the new assessment model.",
        lessons_learned: "We would build the real-time assessment and feedback components into the original research partnership from day one, so that surveys, administrative data, and performance measures were explicitly designed to feed a student-facing tool. We would also co-design more elements with students and employers early on to streamline adoption and reduce friction during implementation.",
        recognition: "The underlying co-op research has been supported by the Strada Education Foundation and Ascendium Education Group and presented to Northeastern leadership and external audiences as a model for measuring experiential learning and early labor-market outcomes.",
