        description: "BaseCamp Studio is a structured, time-bound industry-collaborated talent accelerator program that connects graduate students with real organizations to solve authentic, applied problems while developing professional learning and development knowledge and reflective skills. L&D content is delivered over six weeks, and students work in interdisciplinary teams on 4- to 8-week projects spanning areas such as AI, analytics, sustainability, and digital transformation, guided by industry partners and facilitated by career and experiential learning staff. The program integrates coaching, reflection, and feedback to help students translate academic knowledge into workplace-ready capabilities and professional narratives. In FY25, BaseCamp Studio engaged over 25 students and multiple partner organizations, serving as a scalable bridge between coursework, experiential learning, and employability",
