        success_metrics: "BaseCamp Studio’s success is measured through participation, equity of access, skill development, partner engagement, and employment outcomes. Key indicators include strong application-to-selection ratios and completion rates across Basecamp and Studio cohorts; the number of students advancing from Basecamp into paid Studio placements; and demonstrated growth in applied technical and professional skills through completed projects and portfolios. Additional success metrics include partner demand and repeat participation, the volume of interviews leading to Studio placements, and downstream outcomes such as co-op placement rates (e.g., 55–60% for recent cohorts) and students’ ability to translate project work into employment opportunities. Collectively, these measures demonstrate the program’s effectiveness in expanding equitable access to paid experiential learning and accelerating workforce readiness",
