        description: "Most colleges choose between a professional advising model or a faculty advising model–espeically for graduate students. At Bouvé, we have built a hybrid model that combines both strengths. We empower our Program Directors to handle the full range of advising needs while keeping them fully supported and informed by professional advisors. The result? Students get a seamless experience with one trusted point of contact for everything from course selection to career planning.  Our success comes through collaboration and intensive training. Professional advisors and program directors meet monthly and advisors participate in curriculum meetings, ensuring everyone stays aligned. For 2,500 graduate students across 40+ program options (including Plus One and other program pathways) this model delivers high-quality, personalized advising that maximizes our existing resources and puts student experience first.",
        problem_opportunity: "Graduate students consistently told us they were frustrated by \"the shuffle\", being passed from office to office to resolve a single issue. When they reached out to faculty with a problem, they would be directed to an advisor. The advisor would send them to the program directors or to other university offices. We saw this complaint surface repeatedly in university surveys, college surveys, point-of-service surveys, during our student leadership council meetings, on the NU SubReddit, and through other feedback channels. It was not just inconvenient, it was impacting student trust and overall satisfaction with their degree program.  With limited resources to expand our professional advising staff, we asked a different question: How can we empower the program directors that students already trust to handle their needs comprehensively and refer only when the requests are truly out of their scope? Our innovative advising program equips faculty with intensive training including case studies of common scenarios, a Canvas course with all of the resources professional advisors use, and ongoing support from professional advisors, so they feel confident addressing the full spectrum of student concerns. The goal is simple: eliminate the shuffle and give students one knowledgeable point of contact who can actually solve their problems.",
